author: Russell Brand
description:
A man falls in love with his AI chatbot—and proposes. Is this just a quirky news item or a dire warning about where we’re headed? In this episode of Unpacked, we explore what happens when artificial companions replace real connection. From emotional intimacy with algorithms to tech-induced alienation, we ask: are we spiritually starving in a hyper-connected world? What’s being sold to us in the guise of support, and what are we losing in the process?

Today I’m speaking with Erik Prince — former Navy SEAL, founder of Blackwater, and now creator of the Unplugged phone — about the chaos in the Middle East, the rise of private military forces, and what’s really driving conflict between Iran, Israel, and the West. We dig into the role of proxy wars, failed regime change, and the deeper forces behind U.S. foreign policy. But it’s not just about war — we explore how technology is shaping the future of governance, the danger of surveillance capitalism, and why Erik believes decentralization, competition, and faith are key to reclaiming freedom in a collapsing empire.
title: The Truth About Iran, Israel & U.S. War – Erik Prince Breaks It Down - SF603

Trump brokered a ceasefire between Israel and Iran—but it didn’t last. Today we unpack Trump’s explosive reaction as Israel violates the deal, Iran retaliates, and the so-called “12 Day War” reignites. Trump blasts both nations—“they don’t know what the f*ck they’re doing”—while voices across media clash over who's to blame. CNN gets caught mid-spin, Fox News attacks Trump’s peace efforts, and even his own allies begin to splinter. Has Trump lost control of the narrative—or is he the only adult in the room?
